transcriptions:
For me during COVID there were two opposite reactions:
1.fear for friends and family that something can happen with them and I won't be able to help, as much as I could;
2.frustration, that I could help only with some data analysis, rather than with a real physical help;
3.at the same time, i finally had time to work on research projects and articles I could not work on before confinement, i managed to continue and advance some projects with far-away collaborators, since "far" became a bit closer.
